Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Business Designer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-7)

Use the *List *element if you want to create lists with bullets or numbered lists.

Drag the list element onto the template and enter the text, the paragraphs will then be indented and given the standard list format containing simple numbers.

The list element can contain any block-level elements as child elements, e.g. blocks (paragraphs), containers or subordinate lists.

![](data:image/png;base64,)![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Select list format:

- Mark the list in the editor (orange frame!) or select it in the outline.

- Select the list format under *Style &amp; Properties *&lt; *List*. All available list formats of XSL-FO are available as buttons.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

With *Start Index *you can choose a different start value for a numbered list - with normal digits or according to the list format, both are possible.

With *Prefix *and *Suffix *you can add text or characters before and after the number or enumeration symbol.

> Note:

*If you want to insert your own enumeration characters, you could use the prefix and copy special characters from other applications into the field.*

You can control the spacing between page margins and characters or between characters and text under *Advanced *&gt; *Bullets and Numbering*.

> Note:

*Prefix and suffix are displayed superscript to indicate that its not a normal text.*

## List improvements
With Version 6.4 List Element has been extended with following functionalities:

- Transformation of the Block into a List now possible with keyword *Tab*

- Reversing the List creation or List level is now possible with combination *SHIFT+TAB*

(For more information please see all keyboard shortcuts)

- Sublist functionality which inherits the parent numbered item and its suffix. This is done through a specific syntax inside the Prefix Field: ***%inherit***

> Note

It is advisable, when using sublist functionality to have same prefix and List- type in all List children Elements.
